# Rule 03 - Enterprise Event Governance v2
# Part 2 - Event Design

# Event Design Philosophy

Events are immutable business facts.

Events describe

What Happened

Never

What Should Happen

Events are contracts.

Breaking an event contract is equivalent to breaking a public API.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Structure

Every Integration Event must contain

eventId

eventType

eventVersion

aggregateId

aggregateType

tenantId

correlationId

causationId

occurredAt

producer

payload

metadata

Never publish anonymous events.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Metadata

Required Metadata

eventId

correlationId

causationId

tenantId

pluginId

traceId

spanId

producerService

producerVersion

schemaVersion

eventTimestamp

Metadata must be consistent across all services.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Payload

Payload contains only

Business Data

Never include

Database IDs from other services

Internal JPA entities

Repositories

Business logic

Temporary fields

Implementation details

Events are public contracts.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Ownership

Each event has exactly

One Aggregate

One Publisher

One Bounded Context

One Service

One Kafka Topic

One Schema

One Version

Ownership ambiguity is prohibited.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Publication Flow

Aggregate

↓

Business Rule

↓

Domain Event

↓

Application Service

↓

Outbox

↓

Kafka Publisher

↓

Integration Event

↓

Kafka Topic

↓

Consumers

Never publish Integration Events directly from Aggregates.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Domain Event Rules

Domain Events

Remain

Inside

The Bounded Context.

Never publish Domain Events directly to Kafka.

Application Services convert

Domain Events

↓

Integration Events

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Integration Event Rules

Integration Events

Cross

Service Boundaries.

Integration Events are immutable.

Never modify an event after publication.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Versioning

Every event

Starts at

Version 1

Future changes

↓

Version 2

↓

Version 3

Never break existing consumers.

Support parallel versions during migration.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Schema Evolution

Allowed

Add Optional Fields

Add Metadata

Add New Event Versions

Forbidden

Rename Existing Fields

Delete Required Fields

Change Existing Meanings

Reuse Event Names

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Naming

Pattern

BusinessObject

↓

Past Tense

Examples

LeadCreated

LeadQualified

CustomerRegistered

PropertyReserved

InvoicePaid

AppointmentBooked

WorkflowCompleted

