------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Partition Strategy

Partition by

AggregateId

TenantId

Business Key

Choose based on ordering requirements.

Never partition randomly.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Ordering

Ordering is guaranteed

Only

Inside One Partition.

Never assume global ordering.

Business logic must tolerate out-of-order events.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Idempotency

Every consumer

Must be idempotent.

Duplicate events

Must not create duplicate business state.

Store processed event identifiers where required.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Retry Strategy

Every consumer defines

Retry Count

Retry Delay

Exponential Backoff

Maximum Attempts

Failure Strategy

Never retry forever.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Dead Letter Queue

Every topic

Requires

DLQ

Examples

lead.created.dlq

customer.registered.dlq

workflow.failed.dlq

DLQ processing must be observable.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Timeout

Every consumer defines

Maximum Processing Time

Slow events

Generate alerts.

Never allow indefinite processing.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Outbox Pattern

Every Business Service

Owns

One Outbox Table.

Business Transaction

↓

Commit

↓

Outbox

↓

Publisher

↓

Kafka

Outbox guarantees reliable publication.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Inbox Pattern

Consumers

May maintain

Inbox Tables

To guarantee

Exactly Once

Business Processing.

Never depend solely on Kafka delivery semantics.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Saga Integration

Events drive

Saga progression.

Every Saga step

Defines

Forward Event

Compensation Event

Timeout

Retry

Never coordinate Sagas through database transactions.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CQRS

Integration Events

Build

Projection Models

Search Models

Dashboard Models

Analytics Models

Read Models

Never update Aggregates from projections.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Consumers

Consumers

Must

Validate

Schema

Tenant

Permissions

Business Rules

Idempotency

Before processing.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Multi-Tenant Events

Every event

Contains

tenantId

Consumers

Reject

Tenant Mismatch

Cross Tenant Processing

Missing Tenant Context

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Correlation

Every event propagates

traceId

spanId

correlationId

causationId

requestId

tenantId

Never lose distributed traceability.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Contracts

Events are

Backward Compatible

Documented

Versioned

Tested

Observable

Treat event contracts like REST contracts.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Contract Testing

Every published Integration Event

Requires

Schema Validation

Consumer Contract Tests

Backward Compatibility Tests

Never publish untested event contracts.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Security

Never publish

Passwords

JWT

Secrets

API Keys

Private Documents

Sensitive PII

Use identifiers rather than confidential payloads.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Review Checklist

Before publishing verify

✓ Aggregate Owner

✓ Bounded Context

✓ Integration Event

✓ Version

✓ Topic

✓ Metadata

✓ TenantId

✓ CorrelationId

✓ Outbox

✓ Idempotency

