# Rule 03 - Enterprise Event Governance v2
# Part 4 - Event Governance & Repository Intelligence

# Event Governance Philosophy

Events are public contracts.

Once published

Consumers depend on them.

Changing an event without governance is an architectural defect.

Events must evolve safely.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Lifecycle

Every event follows

Draft

↓

Architecture Review

↓

Approved

↓

Implemented

↓

Published

↓

Consumed

↓

Monitored

↓

Deprecated

↓

Retired

Never publish undocumented events.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Registry

Every published event must be registered.

The Event Registry contains

Event Name

Description

Category

Owner

Publisher

Consumers

Aggregate

Bounded Context

Kafka Topic

Schema Version

Retention Policy

Retry Policy

DLQ Policy

Security Classification

Tenant Scope

Plugin Scope

Documentation Link

The Event Registry is the authoritative source for event contracts.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Ownership

Each event has exactly one

Business Owner

Technical Owner

Publishing Service

Owning Aggregate

Owning Bounded Context

Owning Kafka Topic

Never allow shared ownership.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Repository Intelligence

Before creating a new event

Search the repository.

Check for

Existing Event

Existing Topic

Existing Schema

Existing Consumer

Existing Aggregate

Existing Workflow

Existing Integration

Existing Plugin Event

Existing AI Event

Reuse existing contracts whenever possible.

Never create duplicate business events.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Review Questions

Before approving a new event answer

1. Is this a business fact?

2. Does an equivalent event already exist?

3. Which Aggregate owns it?

4. Which Bounded Context owns it?

5. Which Service publishes it?

6. Which Topic carries it?

7. Which consumers depend on it?

8. Is versioning required?

9. Is tenant isolation preserved?

10. Does this increase coupling?

If ownership is unclear

Reject the event.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Schema Governance

Every Integration Event

Must have

Schema

Version

Compatibility Policy

Documentation

Validation Rules

Examples

JSON Schema

Avro

Protobuf

Never publish undocumented payloads.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Compatibility Rules

Allowed

Add optional fields

Add metadata

Create new event versions

Deprecate gradually

Forbidden

Rename required fields

Remove required fields

Change business meaning

Reuse old event names

Breaking changes require a new version.

